HOW TO USE FERN.JS
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
lib/Fern.js is not a proper node.js module.  It is intended to be used
dominantly on web pages, where it is included like any other JavaScript file.
To use it in a node.js project, you can use this approach:

  eval(require('fs').readFileSync('lib/Fern.js', 'utf8'));


HOW TO USE FERN
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Edible documentation lives at the top of lib/Fern.js.


HOW TO TEST
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Install Buster.js:

  npm install buster -g
  npm link buster


Run the tests:

  buster test --reporter tap

OR

  node test/fern-test.js


HOW TO DEBUG
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Typical node.js debugging:

  node debug test/fern-test.js


The "debugger;" statement in debugged code is a software breakpoint.

